WEBVTT

00:00.917 --> 00:02.836
PREVIOUSLY ON "NYPD BLUE"...

00:03.628 --> 00:06.548
JOHNNY, I'VE ALWAYS LOVED YOU.
YOU'RE MY SON.

00:06.589 --> 00:07.882
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

00:07.882 --> 00:09.718
CAN WE LEAVE IT AT THAT?

00:09.718 --> 00:11.261
OKAY.

00:11.261 --> 00:13.930
I'M NOT TRYING TO GET US
AHEAD OF OURSELVES.

00:13.930 --> 00:16.891
HOWEVER LONG THIS LASTS,
I JUST WANT TO ENJOY IT.

00:16.891 --> 00:18.059
THAT'S GOOD FOR ME.

00:29.070 --> 00:30.613
CAN YOU STAY AWHILE?

00:31.573 --> 00:33.324
I'LL STAY AS LONG
AS YOU NEED.

00:35.243 --> 00:37.245
ME AND CONNIE ARE TAKING THEO TO
DISNEY WORLD,

00:37.662 --> 00:40.415
SO IF THERE'S ANY COMMENTS,
ANY BALL-BUSTING,

00:40.498 --> 00:42.042
ANYBODY GOT A PROBLEM WITH IT,
GET IT OUT NOW.

00:44.085 --> 00:45.462
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

00:58.224 --> 01:01.102
WELCOME BACK, DETECTIVE.
HOW WAS THE TRIP?

01:01.102 --> 01:02.187
GOOD.

01:02.187 --> 01:03.730
DID THEO HAVE FUN?

01:03.730 --> 01:05.607
HE WANTED TO MOVE THERE.

01:05.607 --> 01:06.775
HERE. HE INSISTED.

01:06.775 --> 01:08.902
DON'T FEEL OBLIGATED
TO WEAR THEM.

01:08.902 --> 01:11.279
I HAVEN'T HAD MICKEY EARS
SINCE I WAS 4!

01:11.279 --> 01:12.906
THAT'S MOST RATIONAL PEOPLE.

01:12.906 --> 01:15.700
TELL THEO IT WAS SO SWEET OF HIM
TO THINK OF ME.

01:15.700 --> 01:18.453
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'LL WRITE HIM A NOTE.

01:18.453 --> 01:20.705
HE'LL GET A KICK
OUT OF THAT.

01:20.705 --> 01:23.083
UH, YOU CAN LOSE THE EARS
NOW.

01:23.083 --> 01:25.960
ANDY, WELCOME BACK. HOW WAS
YOUR TRIP?

01:25.960 --> 01:27.670
GOOD.

01:27.670 --> 01:29.214
I GOT THIS ON THE WAY IN --
MISSING KID.

01:29.214 --> 01:31.925
MOM'S AT THE APARTMENT --
1st AND 4th.

01:31.925 --> 01:33.051
WHERE'S McDOWELL?

01:33.051 --> 01:34.636
ON HER WAY IN, I GUESS.

01:34.636 --> 01:37.055
PAGE HER AND THE OTHERS. HAVE
THEM RESPOND.

01:37.055 --> 01:38.306
GOOD TO HAVE YOU BACK.

01:38.306 --> 01:39.682
THANKS.

01:39.682 --> 01:41.935
THE MAN RETURNS.

01:41.935 --> 01:44.187
THUMBS UP, SIPOWICZ.

01:45.230 --> 01:47.232
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED
TO MEAN?

01:47.232 --> 01:48.650
I DON'T KNOW, DETECTIVE.

01:51.361 --> 01:52.529
KEEP THOSE HID.

02:01.913 --> 02:03.832
HEY.

02:06.501 --> 02:08.336
WELCOME BACK. THANKS.

02:08.336 --> 02:09.629
HAD A GOOD TRIP?

02:09.629 --> 02:11.965
YEAH.
YOU TALK TO THE MOM?

02:11.965 --> 02:14.092
I JUST WALKED IN.
NAME'S CATHERINE LOWE.

02:14.092 --> 02:15.593
SON -- SCOTT, 12 YEARS OLD.

02:15.593 --> 02:18.388
HIS BED WASN'T SLEPT IN.
HE'S NEVER RUN AWAY BEFORE.

02:18.388 --> 02:21.057
ANY CHANCE HE MADE THE BED
AND DUCKED OUT EARLY?

02:21.057 --> 02:22.517
SHE SAYS IT DOESN'T HAPPEN.

02:22.517 --> 02:23.726
WHERE'S EVERYBODY ELSE?

02:23.726 --> 02:25.937
JONES AND MEDAVOY STARTED A
SEARCH OF THE BUILDING.

02:25.937 --> 02:27.480
STILL WAITING ON McDOWELL AND
ORTIZ.

02:29.399 --> 02:31.401
DETECTIVES SIPOWICZ
AND CLARK, MRS. LOWE.

02:31.401 --> 02:33.444
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW YOUR SON?

02:33.444 --> 02:35.738
LAST NIGHT BEFORE I WENT OUT --
8:00, I GUESS.

02:35.738 --> 02:36.906
WHERE'D YOU GO?

02:36.906 --> 02:38.700
O'DELL'S -- MET MY
GIRLFRIENDS.

02:38.700 --> 02:40.368
WHAT TIME DID YOU
COME HOME?

02:40.368 --> 02:41.578
ABOUT 2:00.

02:41.578 --> 02:43.621
IT'S NORMAL YOU DON'T CHECK ON
HIM?

02:43.621 --> 02:45.039
I DIDN'T WANT TO WAKE HIM.

02:45.039 --> 02:47.667
WERE YOU IN ANY KIND OF
ARGUMENT WITH YOUR SON?

02:47.667 --> 02:49.002
WAS HE BEING DISCIPLINED?

02:49.002 --> 02:50.211
NO.

02:50.211 --> 02:52.172
HE'S DRINKING OR DOING
DRUGS AT ALL?

02:52.172 --> 02:54.674
NOTHING LIKE THAT.
HE'S A COMPUTER KID.

02:54.674 --> 02:56.968
DOES ANYBODY ELSE HAVE ACCESS TO
YOUR PLACE?

02:56.968 --> 02:59.762
IS THERE ANYPLACE YOU CAN THINK
OF HE MIGHT HAVE GONE?

02:59.762 --> 03:02.432
MAYBE HE'S AT THE DWYERS'.
MAYBE HIS FATHER TOOK HIM.

03:02.432 --> 03:05.310
I DON'T KNOW, 'CAUSE NOBODY'S
ANSWERING THEIR DAMN PHONE.

03:05.310 --> 03:07.562
WE'LL LOOK INTO IT.
WHERE'S HIS FATHER LIVE?

03:07.562 --> 03:08.730
PARK SLOPE.

03:08.730 --> 03:11.733
IF HE TOOK SCOTT, YOU TELL HIM I
WILL KILL HIM.

03:11.733 --> 03:13.735
SO THINGS AREN'T GOOD
BETWEEN YOU?

03:13.735 --> 03:15.069
A BAD DIVORCE.

03:15.069 --> 03:16.404
AND THE DWYERS?

03:16.404 --> 03:18.698
THAT'S SCOTT'S FRIEND JAKE.
THEY LIVE NEARBY.

03:18.698 --> 03:21.701
WHY DON'T YOU WRITE DOWN THEIR
PHONE AND ADDRESS --

03:21.701 --> 03:23.036
THE DWYERS AND YOUR EX?

03:23.036 --> 03:25.663
AND ANY OTHER PLACE
YOU THINK WE SHOULD LOOK.

03:25.663 --> 03:27.290
LET'S CATCH UP McDOWELL.

03:28.791 --> 03:29.959
HEY.

03:29.959 --> 03:31.502
CONNIE, WELCOME BACK.

03:31.502 --> 03:33.296
THANKS.
HOW'S IT LOOKING?

03:33.296 --> 03:36.049
KID'S NEVER RUN OFF.
THEY WEREN'T IN A FIGHT.

03:36.049 --> 03:39.052
AND CAN'T FIND THE DIVORCED DAD.
HE'S FIRST STOP.

03:39.052 --> 03:41.888
MEANTIME, GET UNIFORM ON
SEARCHING THE AREA --

03:41.888 --> 03:43.306
VACANT LOTS, BASEMENTS.

03:43.306 --> 03:44.432
WE'D BETTER, YEAH.

03:47.936 --> 03:49.520
WHAT IS IT, PAL?

03:49.520 --> 03:51.064
HOW WAS FLORIDA?

03:51.064 --> 03:52.857
SO THE WORLD KNOWS?

03:52.857 --> 03:54.025
GOT AROUND.

03:54.025 --> 03:56.027
FLORIDA WAS FINE, PAL.

03:56.027 --> 03:57.612
NOW EXPLAIN THAT SMIRK.

03:57.612 --> 04:01.532
ANDY...YOU'RE MY HERO.

05:17.108 --> 05:18.443
ANYTHING?

05:18.443 --> 05:20.403
NO ONE IN THE AREA
HAD SEEN THE KID.

05:20.403 --> 05:23.114
NONE OF THE NEIGHBORS SAW
ANYTHING OUT OF THE ORDINARY.

05:23.114 --> 05:24.615
ANY LUCK FINDING
THE DAD?

05:24.615 --> 05:26.326
NO ONE ANSWERED
AT HIS HOUSE,

05:26.326 --> 05:28.619
AND APPARENTLY,
HE'S TAKING A DAY OFF WORK.

05:28.619 --> 05:30.330
PLANNED OR
UR-OF-THE-MOMENT?

05:30.330 --> 05:31.998
PUT IN FOR IT
TWO WEEKS AGO.

05:31.998 --> 05:33.958
WE'RE GONNA TALK TO HIS
CO-WORKERS.

05:33.958 --> 05:35.168
TOMMY DWYER.

05:35.168 --> 05:38.963
I GOT A MESSAGE TO SEE
DETECTIVES CLARK OR SIPOWICZ.

05:38.963 --> 05:41.716
YEAH -- ANDY SIPOWICZ.
JOHN CLARK.

05:41.716 --> 05:43.259
LET'S TALK BACK HERE.

05:45.303 --> 05:47.055
DAD OF THE MISSING KID'S
FRIEND.

05:47.055 --> 05:49.724
SO THE MISSING KID'S FATHER'S
YOUR ANGLE?
FOR NOW.

05:49.724 --> 05:52.727
I DON'T GOTTA TELL YOU WE GOTTA
COVER THESE BASES IN A HURRY.

05:52.727 --> 05:53.770
NO, YOU DON'T.

05:55.897 --> 05:58.066
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
MAKE THIS QUICK --

05:58.066 --> 05:59.734
WITH A MISSING KID
AND ALL.

05:59.734 --> 06:02.862
I KNOW. I WAS JUST TELLING HIM.
I'M RETIRED OFF THE JOB.

06:02.862 --> 06:04.030
20 YEARS, HIGHWAY 1.

06:04.030 --> 06:05.865
YOUR SON AND SCOTT
ARE FRIENDS?

06:05.865 --> 06:07.158
SINCE THEY WERE LITTLE.

06:07.158 --> 06:09.035
HE SPEND TIME AT YOUR
APARTMENT?

06:09.035 --> 06:10.203
YEAH, HE COMES OVER.

06:10.203 --> 06:12.163
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW HIM?

06:12.163 --> 06:14.791
TWO DAYS AGO. ARE YOU THINKING
HE WAS KIDNAPPED?

06:14.791 --> 06:16.751
WE'RE STILL TRYING TO PUT IT
TOGETHER.

06:16.751 --> 06:18.002
HE SAYS HE COMES OVER.

06:18.002 --> 06:20.129
DOES THAT MEAN YOUR SON AND
SCOTT ARE CLOSE,

06:20.129 --> 06:21.297
OR ARE THEY JUST PALS?

06:21.297 --> 06:22.423
FAIRLY CLOSE, I GUESS.

06:22.423 --> 06:24.133
ANY CHANCE
THEY'RE TOGETHER NOW?

06:24.133 --> 06:25.301
NO. JAKE'S AT SCHOOL.

06:25.301 --> 06:28.137
I CHECKED UP
AFTER I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.

06:28.137 --> 06:30.640
YOU'RE NOT THINKING THIS IS
WORSE THAN KIDNAPPING.

06:30.640 --> 06:32.475
WE'RE JUST GETTING
OFF THE GROUND.

06:32.475 --> 06:34.477
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT SCOTT'S FAMILY?

06:34.477 --> 06:36.145
UH...THE MOM'S
A LITTLE ROUGH.

06:36.145 --> 06:38.731
I MEAN, I DON'T WANT TO SAY
NOTHING BAD AGAINST HER.

06:38.731 --> 06:39.899
HEY, A KID IS MISSING.

06:39.899 --> 06:41.651
YOU GOT SOMETHING,
LET'S HEAR IT.

06:41.651 --> 06:45.655
SCOTT WASN'T EXACTLY THRILLED
WITH HIS HOME LIFE.

06:45.655 --> 06:46.864
SPECIFICALLY?

06:46.864 --> 06:48.324
CATHY ISN'T AROUND A LOT,

06:48.324 --> 06:50.493
AND HER ATTENTIONS
ARE ON OTHER THINGS --

06:50.493 --> 06:52.203
YOU KNOW,
HAVING A GOOD TIME.

06:52.203 --> 06:54.163
SCOTT WANTED TO LIVE
WITH HIS DAD.

06:54.163 --> 06:55.331
YEAH, WE HEARD THAT.

06:55.331 --> 06:57.583
BUT I THINK HE WAS READY
TO MAKE THE JUMP

06:57.583 --> 06:59.544
AND HIS DAD
WAS READY TO TAKE HIM.

06:59.544 --> 07:00.962
SCOTT TOLD YOU THIS?

07:00.962 --> 07:03.423
HE DIDN'T HAVE A DAD AT HOME,
SO HE TALKED TO ME.

07:03.423 --> 07:05.133
HE LAY OUT
ANY KIND OF PLAN?

07:05.133 --> 07:07.009
HE REALLY WANTED TO LIVE
WITH HIS DAD,

07:07.009 --> 07:08.970
AND HIS DAD REALLY WANTED
TO TAKE HIM,

07:08.970 --> 07:10.847
AND ONE DAY SOON,
IT WAS GONNA HAPPEN.

07:10.847 --> 07:12.932
HAVE YOU TALKED TO JIM YET --
SCOTT'S DAD?

07:12.932 --> 07:14.642
CAN'T FIND HIM AT HOME
OR AT WORK.

07:14.642 --> 07:16.310
YOU GOT SOMEPLACE ELSE
TO LOOK?

07:16.310 --> 07:18.312
SCOTT MENTIONED
HE PLAYS A LOT OF GOLF

07:18.312 --> 07:19.981
AT A COUNTRY CLUB
IN RIVERDALE.

07:19.981 --> 07:22.358
HE'S GONNA KIDNAP
HIS KID AND PLAY GOLF.

07:22.358 --> 07:24.068
I'M JUST TELLING YOU
WHAT I KNOW.

07:24.152 --> 07:25.695
ALL RIGHT,
THANKS FOR YOUR TIME.

07:28.865 --> 07:30.366
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

07:32.577 --> 07:35.621
HE AIMED IT AT THE DAD --
CUSTODIAL INTERFERENCE.

07:35.621 --> 07:37.498
DO WE HAVE A PLACE
TO LOOK?

07:37.498 --> 07:40.418
A WEAK POSSIBLE, BUT IT MIGHT GO
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

07:40.418 --> 07:42.503
WE'RE ON THE AIR.

07:44.338 --> 07:46.424
MAN DOWNSTAIRS SAID TO TALK
TO A DETECTIVE.

07:46.424 --> 07:47.884
REGARDING WHAT, SIR?

07:47.884 --> 07:50.511
I THINK I HAVE A SUSPECT IN
YOUR MISSING-CHILD CASE.

07:50.511 --> 07:53.222
HOW DO YOU KNOW WE'RE WORKING ON
A MISSING-CHILD CASE?

07:53.222 --> 07:54.932
I MONITOR
THE POLICE FREQUENCY.

07:54.932 --> 07:57.351
WHERE'D YOU FIND
THIS SUSPECT? THE
INTERNET.

07:57.351 --> 07:59.187
THESE DETECTIVES
WILL TALK TO YOU.

08:00.646 --> 08:03.566
IF THERE'S ANYTHING IN IT,
CALL ANDY AND JOHN.

08:03.566 --> 08:05.026
IF NOT, SEND HIM HOME.

08:05.026 --> 08:06.819
COME ON IN. YOUR NAME?

08:06.819 --> 08:07.862
TED MUNTZ.

08:07.862 --> 08:10.698
HAVE A SEAT.

08:10.698 --> 08:12.700
SO, WHAT DO YOU GOT
FOR US, TED?

08:12.700 --> 08:15.536
THESE ARE PRINTOUTS
OF 31 E-MAILS BETWEEN MYSELF

08:15.536 --> 08:18.664
AND AN INDIVIDUAL WHO REFERS TO
HIMSELF AS "FUNTIMES65,"

08:18.664 --> 08:20.082
WHICH IS REPREHENSIBLE,

08:20.082 --> 08:22.668
CONSIDERING WHAT A FOUL-MINDED
PERSON HE IS.

08:22.668 --> 08:25.588
MR. MUNTZ, WE NEED TO ASK YOU
TO CUT TO THE CHASE.

08:25.588 --> 08:28.341
FIRST, I NEED TO TELL YOU
ABOUT A BOY I KNOW --

08:28.341 --> 08:30.551
AARON NESTER --
SCREEN NAME AARON21.

08:30.551 --> 08:32.011
AARON IS 15 YEARS OLD.

08:32.011 --> 08:34.305
HE ATTENDS MT. JEFFERSON HIGH
IN NEW JERSEY.

08:34.305 --> 08:36.766
HE'S IN THE THEATER CLUB,
RUNS CROSS-COUNTRY,

08:36.766 --> 08:39.477
AND HE'S DESPERATELY CONFUSED
ABOUT HIS SEXUALITY.

08:39.477 --> 08:41.854
THING ABOUT AARON THAT'S SO
INTERESTING IS

08:41.854 --> 08:42.980
HE DOESN'T EXIST.

08:42.980 --> 08:45.066
MR. MUNTZ, YOU'VE GOT
ABOUT 30 SECONDS.

08:45.066 --> 08:46.150
AARON NESTER IS ME.

08:46.150 --> 08:48.194
I GO INTO YOUTH-ORIENTED
CHAT ROOMS,

08:48.194 --> 08:50.905
DISGUISED AS AARON, AND
ROOT OUT ONLINE PEDOPHILES.

08:50.905 --> 08:52.365
THIS IS A HOBBY?

08:52.365 --> 08:54.033
I DO TECH SUPPORT,
SO I'M HOME ALL DAY.

08:54.033 --> 08:56.077
I'M JUST MAKING USE
OF MY DOWNTIME.

08:56.077 --> 08:58.663
HAVE YOU BEEN SUCCESSFUL?
HAVE THERE BEEN ARRESTS?

08:58.663 --> 09:00.164
THIS WOULD BE THE FIRST.

09:00.164 --> 09:01.832
SO, WHAT DO YOU GOT,
TED?

09:01.832 --> 09:03.834
ABOUT A MONTH AGO,

09:03.834 --> 09:05.962
THIS FUNTIME LURED AARON
INTO A PRIVATE CHAT ROOM

09:05.962 --> 09:08.839
AND STARTED GRILLING HIM ABOUT
WAS HE A VIRGIN,

09:08.839 --> 09:10.925
HAD HE EVER HAD
A GAY EXPERIENCE

09:10.925 --> 09:13.636
OR FANTASIZED ABOUT BOYS
IN THE LOCKER ROOM,

09:13.636 --> 09:16.055
UNTIL FUNTIME ESSENTIALLY
SEDUCED AARON

09:16.055 --> 09:17.974
INTO FULL-FLEDGED
ONLINE SEX.

09:17.974 --> 09:19.892
ALL PART OF
YOUR CIVIC DUTY.

09:19.892 --> 09:21.769
IF YOU'RE GONNA GET PAST
ANONYMITY,

09:21.769 --> 09:24.230
YOU HAVE TO GAIN TRUST.
DIDN'T HAVE A CHOICE.

09:24.230 --> 09:26.899
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK FUNTIME
HAS TO DO WITH OUR CASE?

09:26.899 --> 09:29.402
HE'S MADE NUMEROUS REFERENCES TO
THE NEIGHBORHOOD,

09:29.402 --> 09:32.822
SO I'M ALMOST CERTAIN HE LIVES
NEAR YOUR MISSING BOY.

09:32.822 --> 09:35.616
HE SAYS HE'S GUIDED OTHER BOYS
INTO THEIR HOMOSEXUALITY

09:35.616 --> 09:37.451
BY HAVING FACE-TO-FACE
MEETINGS --

09:37.451 --> 09:39.870
SOMETHING HE'S BEEN TRYING TO
ARRANGE WITH AARON

09:39.870 --> 09:41.122
FOR THE PAST TWO WEEKS.

09:41.122 --> 09:42.748
AND HE REPEATEDLY TELLS
AARON

09:42.748 --> 09:45.751
HE KNOWS OF A PLACE WHERE HE CAN
EXPRESS HIMSELF SEXUALLY

09:45.751 --> 09:47.712
AND FINALLY BE FREE FROM
CONFUSION.

09:47.712 --> 09:50.339
I MEAN, HE LIVES HERE,
HE'S PICKING UP BOYS HERE.

09:50.339 --> 09:51.757
THAT'S TWO AND TWO, RIGHT?

09:51.757 --> 09:54.343
IT'S WORTH LOOKING INTO.

09:54.343 --> 09:56.137
HOW LONG WOULD IT TAKE TO
ARRANGE A MEETING WITH THIS GUY?

09:56.137 --> 09:58.014
HE TELLS AARON ANYPLACE,
ANYTIME.

09:58.014 --> 09:59.473
FROM WHAT HE'S MENTIONED,

09:59.473 --> 10:02.101
HE WORKS AT HOME AND LIVES NEAR
A VIDEO-GAME ARCADE,

10:02.101 --> 10:04.103
SO ALL AARON HAS TO DO
IS PAGE HIM.

10:04.103 --> 10:06.063
HE PROVIDED THE NUMBER
TWO WEEKS AGO,

10:06.063 --> 10:08.232
AND WITHIN HALF AN HOUR,
THE MEETING'S ON.

10:08.232 --> 10:10.067
WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN HE CALLS BACK --

10:10.067 --> 10:12.403
YOU TALK LIKE A 15-YEAR-OLD,
RAISE YOUR VOICE?

10:12.403 --> 10:14.614
I'VE NEVER GOTTEN AS FAR AS
MEETING ANYONE,

10:14.614 --> 10:16.532
SO I HAVEN'T THOUGHT
THAT FAR AHEAD.

10:16.532 --> 10:19.201
IF THIS IS SOME KIND OF PRANK,
TELL US NOW.

10:19.201 --> 10:22.830
'CAUSE DOWN THE LINE
I FIND OUT YOU'RE LYING,
YOU'RE GOING TO JAIL.

10:22.830 --> 10:24.498
JAIL?

10:24.498 --> 10:26.500
I CAME HERE TO HELP.
IT'S THE TRUTH.

10:26.500 --> 10:28.586
GET A FEMALE IN ANTICRIME
OR A UNIFORM,

10:28.586 --> 10:31.088
SOMEONE WITH A KID'S VOICE
TO ANSWER THE PHONE

10:31.088 --> 10:32.465
WHEN THIS GUY CALLS BACK.

10:32.465 --> 10:33.966
PAGE HIM NOW.

10:33.966 --> 10:35.301
COME WITH US.

10:57.782 --> 10:59.867
DOWN THIS AISLE,
GREEN HAT AND JACKET.

10:59.867 --> 11:01.744
I JUST PAGED THE NUMBER
AGAIN

11:01.744 --> 11:03.621
TO SEE IF IT'S OUR GUY.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.752
POLICE.
YOU'RE COMING WITH US.

11:09.752 --> 11:11.837
I THINK YOU GOT
THE WRONG GUY.

11:11.837 --> 11:15.466
YEAH? WELL, WHAT'S MY DATE OF
BIRTH DOING ON YOUR PAGER?

11:15.466 --> 11:16.801
SAY ONE MORE THING,

11:16.801 --> 11:19.303
YOU'LL BE ON THE GROUND IN
HANDCUFFS.

11:19.303 --> 11:21.597
DID YOU COME HERE
WITH HIM?

11:21.597 --> 11:22.932
DO YOU KNOW HIM?

11:22.932 --> 11:25.476
THEN GET YOUR BUTT TO
SCHOOL.

11:40.282 --> 11:41.659
SIT DOWN, MR. VOLNEY.

11:41.659 --> 11:42.993
NO, I'LL STAND

11:42.993 --> 11:45.538
UNTIL ONE OF YOU THUGS TELLS ME
WHAT'S GOING ON.

11:45.538 --> 11:47.373
HEY, WHAT THE HELL
IS THIS?

11:47.373 --> 11:49.208
WHAT WERE YOU DOING
AT THE ARCADE?

11:49.208 --> 11:51.794
I WAS PLAYING SOME GAMES,
WASTING TIME.

11:51.794 --> 11:53.504
YOU WEREN'T KEEPING
AN APPOINTMENT?

11:53.504 --> 11:54.672
NO.

11:54.672 --> 11:57.341
HOW DO YOU THINK
WE GOT YOUR PAGER NUMBER?

11:57.341 --> 11:58.342
I GOT NO IDEA.

11:58.342 --> 11:59.969
YOU GOOD WITH COMPUTERS?

11:59.969 --> 12:01.929
I DESIGN WEBSITES,
SO, YEAH.

12:01.929 --> 12:03.931
WHAT'S YOUR HANDLE
IN THE CHAT ROOMS?

12:03.931 --> 12:05.433
GANDALF77.
WHAT THE HELL?

12:05.433 --> 12:07.935
YOU GOT ANOTHER NAME
YOU GO BY -- MAYBE FUNTIME?

12:07.935 --> 12:09.270
NO.

12:09.270 --> 12:13.065
VOLNEY, IF YOU THINK ALL COPS
ARE COMPUTER-ILLITERATE MOPES,

12:13.065 --> 12:14.400
I'M SORRY TO TELL YOU

12:14.400 --> 12:17.236
THERE ARE WHOLE DIVISIONS
OF THE DEPARTMENT

12:17.236 --> 12:19.697
DEVOTED TO PORING
THROUGH COMPUTERS.

12:19.697 --> 12:23.159
THEY'LL QUICKLY PROVE THAT
YOUR SCREEN NAME IS FUNTIME.

12:23.159 --> 12:24.702
ALL RIGHT, SO -- SO WHAT?

